'''Kotoshironushi Shrine''' (ことしろぬしじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} enshrined in {{ill|lt=Ichiba-chō Izuki|Q55523753|qid=Q55523753|1=Ichiba-chō Izuki}}, {{ill|lt=Awa|Q791587|qid=Q791587|1=Awa, Tokushima}}, {{ill|lt=Tokushima Prefecture|Q160734|qid=Q160734|1=Tokushima Prefecture}}. It is popularly called "Obbe-san." The precinct is maintained as '''Izuki Rural Park'''.

=== History ===
The founding year is unknown. One tradition says that descendants of {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Takeomi|1=UNKNOWN}}, maternal grandfather of {{ill|lt=Emperor Annei|Q313345|qid=Q313345|1=Emperor Annei}}, led the {{ill|lt=Izumo clan|Q22123990|qid=Q22123990|1=Izumo zoku}} to Izuki in {{ill|lt=Awa Province|Q907457|qid=Q907457|1=Awa Province (Tokushima)}} and enshrined their ancestral deity {{ill|UNKNOWN|qid=Q8009611|lt=Kotoshironushi no Mikoto|1=Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto}} together with ancestress {{ill|lt=Isuzuyori-hime no Mikoto|Q10881557|qid=Q10881557|1=Isuzuyori-hime}}.

In the {{ill|lt=Edo period|Q184963|qid=Q184963|1=Edo period}}, it was called Kotoji Myōjin or Kotoji Daimyōjin.

=== Enshrined deity ===
* {{ill|UNKNOWN|qid=Q8009611|lt=Kotoshironushi no Mikoto|1=Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto}}

=== Subsidiary shrines ===
* Chinju Shrine
* Moroshiki no Kami
* Ōzumi Daimyōjin

=== Access ===
* About 15 minutes by car from {{ill|lt=Tsuchinari Interchange|Q10927770|qid=Q10927770|1=Donari interchange}} on the {{ill|lt=Tokushima Expressway|Q11490216|qid=Q11490216|1=Tokushima Expressway}}.

